I am finishing up the last of my holiday orders and if you would like to be notified when pet portraits are available, you can click the “availability” highlight and add your email. Or visit website and click on the header. 
I will offer double portraits again and this applies to people as well! I would love to make a special portrait you and your pet and you can select a “double portrait”when they are back in stock. Custom requests and questions are always welcome! Leave a question in comments, or send me a dm ✨✨🙏

Testing out new IG photo size, so square is out, I guess?
It’s about the only thing I’ll be able to keep up with because everything especially reels is hard for me. 
I’m going to do a winter collection after the new year and post some videos of full paintings from start to finish. Hope everyone has a great week!

Here’s a special ornament I made with two pups instead of one. This ornamet measures about 4” and each face is about 1” tall. Ornaments make a great gifts and I will add some new mini pet portrait sizes in the New year. 
I will also have pet portraits in oil and watercolor available.
If you would like a special portrait of two or more pets, I can work from several photos. The most important thing to keep in mind is that the angles are the similar (for example, eye level works best) 
Trying to capture multiple pets in one photo can be tricky but it always results in a beautiful layout. So start taking those photos! More is more and multiple photos are always helpful. 
Let me know if you have any questions in the comments!

I’ve added some little landscapes to my shop! Small size 5x7” makes a perfect addition to any space. Comes framed and ready to hang. I love to bring a little of the outside inside.
I was inspired by the beautiful, changing colors of the sky. When you are able to notice a beautiful sunset or sky and it brings you a relaxed feeling and you are able to stop for a moment and appreciate the beauty around you. These little pieces were meant to add that calm feeling to your space.

My first dog, a black lab named Scooter, will forever hold a special place in my heart. She was such a good watchdog and so sweet. 
I’ve been working on some retro style illustrations and was thinking about all of the pets I had growing up. I have a few new paintings coming this week too! 

#dailyproject #100daysofart #dogillustration #retrosupplyco #rememberingmyscooter #dogsofinstagram #foreverinmyheart #blacklabrador #procreate #digitalart

We had a little dachshund growing up named Inky. She would sit up on her hind legs when we would eat and pretty much stayed that way until we were done eating. It was a very successful trick and she became very plump as she got older. 🦴

After living the apartment life for a long time, all I wanted was my own house so I could have a yard and a dog. Then after I bought my first house witha beautiful yard and my best friend 🐶, all I wanted to do was quit my job and stay home with my dog 😂
My latest horse painting. I’ve been working on this one for awhile and I’m so happy to finally have it complete!
I almost forgot to post this little cow. 🌼🌸🌼🌸🌼 Free US shipping on everything!
Here’s the full view of my latest horse painting. 🌞🍃 11x14” oil on panel. Hope everyone has a great weekend!

My old horse Ed was such a big sweetheart. I had him when I was around 16. I have always struggled with my weight and horseback riding was a big reason I lost weight and got in better shape. There is something so special about being around horses and in the barn that makes me relaxed. Getting away from the busy day, out in nature with fresh air is so calming.
I’ve been trying to work on my digital art and it’s harder than it seems! I’m going to practice my dog breeds some cats. Maybe a dog a day?

Digital illustration using @retrosupply papers.

Red-winged blackbirds are found in marshes year-round. They also live in meadows, prairies and fields near ponds. I always see them along the road perching in the tall grass. It seem like once you spot a few they are everywhere. The bright wing is so eye catching.

Hope everyone had a wonderful Christmas and wishing everyone love and happiness in the New Year! 
💜This portrait was given as Christmas gift so I wanted to share. Her name is Violet. I love that name and it’s so perfect for a Weimaraner💜

I’ve always loved mushrooms and gnomes and have collected Christmas ornaments forever. I’ve been seeing so many mushroom things lately I wanted to make a little painting. I have a couple more started that I hope to finish after the holidays. 🍄🍄🍄 do you collect anything?

Something a little different🌙 I’ve wanted to do illustration for awhile and write a children’s book but I never know where to start. I have so many ideas for pictures but the writing is where I struggle. I’m going to make some frogs, unicorns and little fairytale characters I’ve been thinking about. My daughter asked for a unicorn painting for her room and I loved the idea since I’ve been painting horses. This winter is especially cold and blah for me and I think something fun and colorful would be a great project. 🍄🌈✨
More mushrooms 🍄🍄🍄🍄
